<p style="margin: 0cm; font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif;">
	<span style="font-family: verdana, geneva; font-size: 12pt;">
		We have prepared for you 3 error scenarios that may appear in your Zscaler application. Click on the related case to see the detailed solution.
	</span>
</p><br>
	<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%;">
		<tbody style="vertical-align: top;">
			<tr>
				<td>
					<details>
						<summary>
							<span style="font-family: verdana, geneva; font-size: 12pt; cursor: pointer; color: #c00000">
								<strong>
								Case 1. Connection Error 
                                <br>(Basic Troubleshooting)
								</strong>
							<br>
								<img src="/sys_attachment.do?sys_id=e4022227872a8dd0489cfc89cebb358b" width="301" height="214">
							</span>
						</summary>
						<p style="margin: 0in; background: white; font-size: 12pt; font-family: 'verdana', serif;">
							<span style="color: black; font-family: verdana, geneva; font-size: 12pt;">
							<strong>Solution:</strong><br>
							Go to More menu in Zscaler application and click on following options in sequence:<br>
                                <ol style="list-style-position: inside; font-family: verdana, geneva; font-size: 12pt;">
                                    <li>Click on&nbsp;<strong>Update Policy</strong>&nbsp;to renew Zscaler&rsquo;s policies</li>
                                    <li>Click on&nbsp;<strong>Update App</strong> to update application</li>
                                    <li>Click on&nbsp;<strong>Repair App</strong></li>
                                    <li>Click on&nbsp;<strong>Restart Service</strong></li>
                                    <li>Go to&nbsp;<strong>Private Access</strong>&nbsp;(lock icon) and connect to Zscaler again</li>
                                </ol>
							    <br>
                            </span>
							<span style="color: black;"><img src="/sys_attachment.do?sys_id=2c51d62b87e28dd0489cfc89cebb35d9" width="300" height="200" /></span>
						</p>
                    </details>
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>
                    <details>
                        <summary>
                            <span style="font-family: verdana, geneva; font-size: 12pt; cursor: pointer; color: #c00000">
                            <strong>Case 2. Authentication error</strong><br>
                            <img src="/sys_attachment.do?sys_id=367ed2e787e68dd0489cfc89cebb3550" width="300" height="187" />
                            </span>
                        </summary>
                            <span style="font-family: verdana, geneva; font-size: 12pt;">
                            <strong>Solution:</strong>
                                <ol style="list-style-position: inside; font-family: verdana, geneva; font-size: 12pt;">
                                    <li>Open the Zscaler application</li>
                                    <li>Pay attention to the tab &ldquo;Private access&rdquo;, click on &ldquo;Authenticate&rdquo;</li>
                                    <span style="font-family: verdana, geneva; font-size: 12pt;"><img src="/sys_attachment.do?sys_id=5d77562387668dd0489cfc89cebb3500" width="470" height="289" /></span></p>
                                    <li>Follow the OKTA log in by entering your <strong>email</strong> and <strong>password</strong> from your laptop</li>
                                    <li>After the process is finished, the Zscaler will be closed automatically</li>
                                    <li>Open the apps and internet pages &ndash; they should work now</li>
                                </ol>
                            </span>
                    </details>
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>
                    <details>
                        <summary>
                            <span style="font-family: verdana, geneva; font-size: 12pt; cursor: pointer; color: #c00000">
                                <strong> Case 3. Your session is expired due to idle timeout error</strong><br>
                                <img src="/sys_attachment.do?sys_id=45902eaf87e68dd0489cfc89cebb35fb" width="300" height="187"/>
                            </span>
                        </summary>
                            <span style="font-family: verdana, geneva; font-size: 12pt;"> 
                            <strong>Solution:</strong>
                            <ol style="list-style-position: inside; font-family: verdana, geneva; font-size: 12pt;">
                                <li>First step is clicking the BACK arrow</li>
                                <br><img src="/sys_attachment.do?sys_id=e8d716a387668dd0489cfc89cebb354a" width="207" height="145" />
                                <li>Once you receive the login screen again, click on LOGIN button</li>
                                <li>Follow the OKTA log in process by entering your email and password from your laptop</li>
                                <li>After the process is finished, the Zscaler will be closed automatically</li>
                            </ol>
                            </span>
                    </details>
                </td>
            </tr>
